 consuming that protect the environment and promote health and health equity.\n*[http://www.gdrc.org/uem/sustran/sustran-principles.html Guiding Principles to Sustainable Mobility]\n*[http://www.sutp.org/ Sustainable Urban Transport Project - knowledge platform (SUTP)]\n*[http://www.capsut.org/ Capacity Building for Sustainable Urban Transport - open platform for training and e-learning offers (hosted by SUTP)]\n*[http://www.german-sustainable-mobility.de/ German Partnership for Sustainable Mobility (GPSM)]\n*[http://www.itdp.org/ Institute for Transportation and Development Policy (ITDP)]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090219000211/http://www.embarq.org/ EMBARQ - The WRI Center for] Sustainable Transportation\n*[http://www.istp.murdoch.edu.au/ Institute for Sustainability and Technology Policy]\n*[http://www.transport2012.org/ Bridging the Gap: Pathways for transport in the post 2012 process]\n*[http://www.sustainable-mobility.org/ Sustainable-mobility.org: the centre of resources on sustainable transport]\n*[http://www.quest-project.eu/ QUEST project: Quality Management tool for Urban Energy efficient Sustainable Transport]\n*[http://www.ecomobility.org/ EcoMobility Alliance: An ICLEI - Local Governments for Sustainability Initiative on Transport]\n*[http://www.carboun.com/energy/road-to-doha-sustainable-transportation-in-the-middle-east/ Sustainable Transportation in the Middle East] via [http://www.carboun.com/ Carboun]\n*[http://www.fairtransport.eu/ The Ecoliner Fairwinds, a proposed large sailing container vessel]\n*[http://www.greenheartproject.org/ The Greenheart, a proposed small sailing container vessel]\n*[https://www.un.org/climatechange/summit/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/09/TRANSPORT-Action-Plan-UEMI.pdf Transport Action Plan: Urban Electric Mobility Initiative], [[United Nations]], [[2014 UN Climate Summit|Climate Summit 2014]], September 2014\n*[http://documents.worldbank.org/curated/en/2013/01/17782806/turning-right-corner-ensuring-development-through-low-carbon-transport-sector Turning the right corner : ensuring development through a low-carbon transport sector], [[World Bank Group]], May 2013.\n*[http://www.returnloads.net/news/the-future-of-city-haulage/ Is this the future? A more sustainable inner city delivery system]\n*[http://www.sustainablenews.uk/Sustainability/reduce-unnecessary-journeys-and-improve-the-sustainability-of-delivery-fleets/ Improve sustainability of delivery fleets]\n*[http://www.issuelab.org/issues/profile/transportation Transportation Research at IssueLab]\n*[https://www.seforall.org/publications/switching-gears-enabling-access-to-sustainable-urban-mobility Switching Gears: Enabling Access to Sustainable Urban Mobility]\n\n[[Category:Sustainable transport| ]]\n", "name_user": "EdmundT", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePolicies and governance:Spelling", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sustainable_transport"}
{"title_page": "Tejas Club", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n\n|name = {{nowrap|Tejas Club}}\n\n|image_name = Tejas Triangle Color Logo.png\n|image_size = 200px\n |established = 1925 \n | type  = [[Secret society]]\n |city = [[Austin, Texas]]\n|footnotes = }}\nThe '''Tejas Club''' is one of the oldest student organizations at the [[University of Texas at Austin]]. It was founded in 1925, and only has male members. The official purpose of the club is \"to allow our members to live a more complete life by sharing their personalities, abilities and efforts to promote good fellowship and a high standard of conduct among ourselves and our fellow students, to encourage loyalty and usefulness to our school, and to further good scholarship.\"<ref name=RSOdatabase>{{cite web|url=http://deanofstudents.utexas.edu/sa/vieworgs.php?org=452|title=Office of the Dean of Students - Student Activities - Registered Student Organization Database|website=[[University of Texas]]}}{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref> The membership process of the organization is secretive and not open to the public.\n\n==Establishment==\n\nThe Tejas Club was formed in 1925 by Tom Renfro and Howell Cobb with the vision of establishing \"a club on this campus composed of men whom we believe to be honorable.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tejasclub.org/history-1/|title=Tejas Club - History|publisher=}}</ref>\nIn its early years, Tejas was associated with [[Theta Nu Epsilon]] (\u0398\u039d\u0395), a nationwide sophomore class society which also included such organizations as [[Skull and Bones]] at [[Yale University]], and [[The Machine (social group)|The Machine]] at the [[University of Alabama]].<ref>[[Theta Nu Epsilon]]</ref>\n\n==On Campus==\n\nTejas members have always been a highly involved and diverse group of men at the University of Texas. Members of the Tejas Club have served as student body presidents and vice presidents, head cheerleaders, Texas Cowboys, Silver Spurs, Texas Blazers, leadership within the Longhorn Band, chairmen of the University Union board of directors, and many other important roles on campus.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailytexanonline.com/news/2014/02/28/rady-and-strickland-elected-student-government-president-and-vice-president|title=Rady, Strickland elected Student Government president, vice president in tight contest|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailytexanonline.com/news/2011/09/16/ut-organizations-rally-to-rename-student-activity-center|title=UT organizations rally to rename Student Activity Center|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailytexanonline.com/2011/04/05/a-farewell-from-student-government|title=A farewell from Student Government|publisher=}}</ref><ref name=\"texasexes.org\">{{cite web|url=http://www.texasexes.org/about/heritage/index.asp?p=540|title=History and Traditions|work=Texas Exes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailytexanonline.com/news/2013/02/14/student-government-profile-horacio-villarreal-and-ugeo-williams|title=Student Government Profile: Horacio Villarreal and Ugeo Williams|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.utexas.edu/universityunions/info/university-unions-board|title=University Unions Board of Directors|publisher=}}</ref><ref>https://www.dailytexanonline.com/2019/03/08/camron-goodman-amie-jean-named-student-body-president-vice-president-by-overwhelming</ref>\n\nThe Tejas Club celebrated its 90th anniversary on September 5 and 6 of 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tejasalumni.org/events/event_details.asp?id=402908|title=Tejas Foundation|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://jimnicar.com/links/why-is-there-a-tejas-club-2/|title=Why is there a Tejas Club?|work=The UT History Corner}}</ref>\n\nSince the early 1930s, the Tejas Club has hosted a weekly speaker series called Tejas Coffee. As is tradition, Tejas Coffees serve as an opportunity for students to interact with influential members of their community in an inviting setting, every Thursday evening. Recent speakers have included UT professor and actor [[Matthew McConaughey]], [[Texas Longhorns]] athletics coaches [[Mack Brown]], [[Rick Barnes]], [[Shaka Smart]]<ref>http://www.dailytexanonline.com/2019/10/18/freshmen-adjust-to-new-life-as-student-athletes</ref><ref>https://twitter.com/TejasClub/status/1182697066105102336?s=20</ref>, [[Tom Herman (American football)|Tom Herman]]<ref>http://www.dailytexanonline.com/2017/02/24/hundreds-cram-into-tejas-houses-front-yard-to-see-tom-herman</ref>, and [[Augie Garrido]]; Founder of Alamo Drafthouse Cinema, [[Tim League]]<ref>https://www.facebook.com/events/397452707873955/</ref>; Former World No. 1 tennis player, [[Andy Roddick]]<ref>http://www.dailytexanonline.com/2019/03/10/students-come-together-to-hear-from-tennis-player-andy-roddick-at-tejas-coffee</ref>; UT professors [[Robert Metcalfe]], [[H.W. Brands]], and [[Larry Speck]]; current UT president [[Gregory L. Fenves]] <ref>https://twitter.com/gregfenves/status/1118881145616257024</ref>and former UT presidents [[William C. Powers]] and [[Larry Faulkner]]; former [[University of Texas System]] chancellor [[Mark Yudof]]; former [[Secretary of the Air Force]] [[Hans Mark]]; former [[National Security Agency]] director [[Bobby Ray Inman]]; Celebrity Chef, [[Tyson Cole]] <ref>https://www.instagram.com/p/B3PrWNKlDqU/</ref>; Whole Foods CEO, [[John Mackey (businessman)|John Mackey]]<ref>https://www.facebook.com/events/160219108249888/</ref>; Cyclist [[Lance Armstrong]]<ref>https://www.dailytexanonline.com/2015/10/02/tejas-club-hosts-lance-armstrong-in-weekly-speaker-series</ref>, and Texas politicians [[Beto O'Rourke]]<ref>https://www.dailytexanonline.com/2017/09/25/beto-orourke-tells-students-about-his-life-plans-for-immigration-reform</ref>, [[Wendy Davis (politician)|Wendy Davis]], James Talarico, [[Christi Craddick]], [[Kel Seliger]], and [[Carole Keeton Strayhorn]] among others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mo.austin360.com/blogs/content/shared-gen/blogs/austin/outandabout/entries/2009/09/09/the_tejas_club.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-04-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195809/http://mo.austin360.com/blogs/content/shared-gen/blogs/austin/outandabout/entries/2009/09/09/the_tejas_club.html |archivedate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Alumni==\n\nMany notable alumni of the University of Texas are Tejas Braves. The Tejas Foundation was created in 1953 to establish communication between former and current members of the club. To this day, the alumni of Tejas continue to be involved with helping the club provide housing, encourage scholarship, and organize various events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tejasclub.org/foundationabout/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-10-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123004910/http://tejasclub.org/foundationabout/ |archivedate=2013-11-23 }}</ref>\n\nAlumni of the Tejas Club include:\n* [[Hook 'em Horns|Harley Clark]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://texassports.com/sports/2013/7/28/traditions_0728135417.aspx?id=270|title=Texas Longhorns Athletics - Traditions: Hook 'em, Horns hand signal|publisher=}}</ref> former judge, attorney, and UT student body president; creator of the \"Hook 'em Horns\" hand sign.<ref name=\"texasexes.org\"/>\n* [[Frank C. Cooksey]], former [[Mayor]] of [[Austin]], [[Texas]]. \n* Alex Cranberg, University of Texas System regent; founder and chairman of Aspect Holdings, LLC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/christopherhelman/2012/09/13/whos-the-texas-oilman-behind-the-newest-iraqi-gusher/|title=Newest Iraqi Gusher Could Make Texas Oilman A Billionaire|author=Christopher Helman|date=13 September 2012|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utsystem.edu/board-of-regents/current-regents/alex-m-cranberg|title=Regent Alex M. Cranberg - University of Texas System|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MuMDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA17&lpg=PA17&dq=alex+cranberg+tejas&source=bl&ots=-gciWbsPj2&sig=4YdnAEanlcyNjNWDkh9pG2SdRdA&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pbFsUeCQOcXaygGgk4HoCQ&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=alex%20cranberg%20tejas&f=false|title=The Alcalde|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Robert H. Dedman, Sr.]],<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2002/08/21/obituaries/21DEDM.html</ref> former billionaire, founder and chairman of [[ClubCorp]], and owner of the [[Pinehurst Resort]].<ref>http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1016181/index.htm</ref>\n* [[Michael L Gillette|Michael L. Gillette]],<ref>[[Michael L Gillette]]</ref> author, historian, and non-profit executive.<ref>http://www.statesman.com/news/lifestyles/oral-history-rekindles-lady-bird-johnsons-voice/nTHTx/</ref>\n* [[W. Page Keeton]],<ref>[[W. Page Keeton]]</ref> former attorney and dean of the [[University of Texas School of Law]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utexas.edu/faculty/council/1999-2000/memorials/Keeton/keeton.html|title=Office of the General Faculty Home Page|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tarlton.law.utexas.edu/exhibits/early_deans/keeton.html|title=Tarlton Law Library - First Year Societies- online exhibit|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Royce C. Lamberth]],<ref>[[Royce C. Lamberth]]</ref> current Senior Judge and former Chief Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of Columbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dcd.uscourts.gov/dcd/lamberth|title=Chief Judge Royce C Lamberth|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100707053848/http://www.dcd.uscourts.gov/dcd/lamberth|archivedate=2010-07-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://endowments.giving.utexas.edu/page/lamberth-judge-roycetejas-schl/3925/|title=Judge Royce C. Lamberth/Tejas Scholarship|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Austin Ligon]],<ref>[[Austin Ligon]]</ref> co-founder and former president and CEO of [[CarMax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utexas.edu/cola/progs/plan2/news/1180|title=UT College of Liberal Arts:|date=12 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lifeandletters.la.utexas.edu/2011/11/to-the-moon/|title=To the Moon \u2039 Life & Letters Magazine|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Steve Poizner]],<ref>[[Steve Poizner]]</ref> businessman, entrepreneur, and [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/590/000207966/|title=Steve Poizner|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wn.com/steve_poizner_on_encore_career_institute|title=Steve Poizner On Encore Career Institute|work=World News}}</ref>\n* [[Rex Tillerson]],<ref>[[Rex Tillerson]]</ref> former [[United States Secretary of State]], former chairman, president, and CEO of [[Exxon Mobil Corporation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/rex-tillerson/|title=Rex Tillerson|author=Christopher Helman|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0-MDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA47&lpg=PA47&dq=rex+tillerson+tejas&source=bl&ots=8p9tMtRCaG&sig=hb_UTSYPbsR5a8V8I2zXM0jU_7Y&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ibFsUcTLMKHXygHd-oGQDA&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=rex%20tillerson%20tejas&f=false|title=The Alcalde|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Malcolm Wallace]],<ref name=\"Valley Morning Star; October 24, 1951\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=TU EX-Student Leader Jailed In Slaying; Malcolm E. Wallace Charged in Death of Golf Professional |work=Valley Morning Star |location=Harlingen, Texas |date=October 24, 1951 |page=1 }}</ref> former UT student body president, [[economist]] for the [[United States Department of Agriculture]],<ref name=\"Jones\">{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Garth |author-link1= |date=August 14, 1985 |title=Federal Official's Death Certificate Ordered Changed |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=l1wdAAAAIBAJ&sjid=E1kEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6821%2C3251761 |newspaper=The Victoria Advocate |location=Victoria, Texas |agency=AP |page=8A |accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref> and press secretary to then-[[United States Senator]] [[Lyndon B. Johnson]].<ref name=\"Dalton\">{{cite web |url=http://www.golftexas.com/departments/coursereviews/butler-pitch-putt.htm |title=Butler Pitch and Putt in Austin: Murder in the clubhouse, fun on the golf course |last1=Dalton |first1=Kyle |date= |website=www.golftexas.com |publisher= |accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Collegiate secret societies in North America]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official|http://tejasclub.org/}}\n\n{{University of Texas at Austin|studentlife}}\n\n[[Category:Collegiate secret societies]]\n[[Category:Student societies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Student organizations established in 1925]]\n[[Category:University of Texas at Austin]]\n[[Category:1925 establishments in Texas]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n\n|name = {{nowrap|Tejas Club}}\n\n|image_name = Tejas Triangle Color Logo.png\n|image_size = 200px\n |established = 1925 \n | type  = [[Secret society]]\n |city = [[Austin, Texas]]\n|footnotes = }}\nThe '''Tejas Club''' is one of the oldest student organizations at the [[University of Texas at Austin]]. It was founded in 1925, and only has male members. The official purpose of the club is \"to allow our members to live a more complete life by sharing their personalities, abilities and efforts to promote good fellowship and a high standard of conduct among ourselves and our fellow students, to encourage loyalty and usefulness to our school, and to further good scholarship.\"<ref name=RSOdatabase>{{cite web|url=http://deanofstudents.utexas.edu/sa/vieworgs.php?org=452|title=Office of the Dean of Students - Student Activities - Registered Student Organization Database|website=[[University of Texas]]}}{{dead link|date=May 2019}}</ref> The membership process of the organization is secretive and not open to the public.\n\n==Establishment==\n\nThe Tejas Club was formed in 1925 by Tom Renfro and Howell Cobb with the vision of establishing \"a club on this campus composed of men whom we believe to be honorable.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://tejasclub.or