lDqU/</ref>; Whole Foods CEO, [[John Mackey (businessman)|John Mackey]]<ref>https://www.facebook.com/events/160219108249888/</ref>; Cyclist [[Lance Armstrong]]<ref>https://www.dailytexanonline.com/2015/10/02/tejas-club-hosts-lance-armstrong-in-weekly-speaker-series</ref>, and Texas politicians [[Beto O'Rourke]]<ref>https://www.dailytexanonline.com/2017/09/25/beto-orourke-tells-students-about-his-life-plans-for-immigration-reform</ref>, [[Wendy Davis (politician)|Wendy Davis]], James Talarico, [[Christi Craddick]], [[Kel Seliger]], and [[Carole Keeton Strayhorn]] among others.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mo.austin360.com/blogs/content/shared-gen/blogs/austin/outandabout/entries/2009/09/09/the_tejas_club.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-04-16 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131029195809/http://mo.austin360.com/blogs/content/shared-gen/blogs/austin/outandabout/entries/2009/09/09/the_tejas_club.html |archivedate=2013-10-29 }}</ref>\n\n==Alumni==\n\nMany notable alumni of the University of Texas are Tejas Braves. The Tejas Foundation was created in 1953 to establish communication between former and current members of the club. To this day, the alumni of Tejas continue to be involved with helping the club provide housing, encourage scholarship, and organize various events.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://tejasclub.org/foundationabout/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2013-10-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131123004910/http://tejasclub.org/foundationabout/ |archivedate=2013-11-23 }}</ref>\n\nAlumni of the Tejas Club include:\n* [[Hook 'em Horns|Harley Clark]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://texassports.com/sports/2013/7/28/traditions_0728135417.aspx?id=270|title=Texas Longhorns Athletics - Traditions: Hook 'em, Horns hand signal|publisher=}}</ref> former judge, attorney, and UT student body president; creator of the \"Hook 'em Horns\" hand sign.<ref name=\"texasexes.org\"/>\n* [[Frank C. Cooksey]], former [[Mayor]] of [[Austin]], [[Texas]]. \n* Alex Cranberg, University of Texas System regent; founder and chairman of Aspect Holdings, LLC.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/christopherhelman/2012/09/13/whos-the-texas-oilman-behind-the-newest-iraqi-gusher/|title=Newest Iraqi Gusher Could Make Texas Oilman A Billionaire|author=Christopher Helman|date=13 September 2012|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utsystem.edu/board-of-regents/current-regents/alex-m-cranberg|title=Regent Alex M. Cranberg - University of Texas System|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=MuMDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA17&lpg=PA17&dq=alex+cranberg+tejas&source=bl&ots=-gciWbsPj2&sig=4YdnAEanlcyNjNWDkh9pG2SdRdA&hl=en&sa=X&ei=pbFsUeCQOcXaygGgk4HoCQ&ved=0CDUQ6AEwAQ#v=onepage&q=alex%20cranberg%20tejas&f=false|title=The Alcalde|publisher=}}</ref>\n*[[Robert H. Dedman, Sr.]],<ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2002/08/21/obituaries/21DEDM.html</ref> former billionaire, founder and chairman of [[ClubCorp]], and owner of the [[Pinehurst Resort]].<ref>http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1016181/index.htm</ref>\n* [[Michael L Gillette|Michael L. Gillette]],<ref>[[Michael L Gillette]]</ref> author, historian, and non-profit executive.<ref>http://www.statesman.com/news/lifestyles/oral-history-rekindles-lady-bird-johnsons-voice/nTHTx/</ref>\n* [[W. Page Keeton]],<ref>[[W. Page Keeton]]</ref> former attorney and dean of the [[University of Texas School of Law]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utexas.edu/faculty/council/1999-2000/memorials/Keeton/keeton.html|title=Office of the General Faculty Home Page|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://tarlton.law.utexas.edu/exhibits/early_deans/keeton.html|title=Tarlton Law Library - First Year Societies- online exhibit|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Royce C. Lamberth]],<ref>[[Royce C. Lamberth]]</ref> current Senior Judge and former Chief Judge of the [[United States District Court for the District of Columbia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dcd.uscourts.gov/dcd/lamberth|title=Chief Judge Royce C Lamberth|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100707053848/http://www.dcd.uscourts.gov/dcd/lamberth|archivedate=2010-07-07}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://endowments.giving.utexas.edu/page/lamberth-judge-roycetejas-schl/3925/|title=Judge Royce C. Lamberth/Tejas Scholarship|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Austin Ligon]],<ref>[[Austin Ligon]]</ref> co-founder and former president and CEO of [[CarMax]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.utexas.edu/cola/progs/plan2/news/1180|title=UT College of Liberal Arts:|date=12 April 2016|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://lifeandletters.la.utexas.edu/2011/11/to-the-moon/|title=To the Moon \u2039 Life & Letters Magazine|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Steve Poizner]],<ref>[[Steve Poizner]]</ref> businessman, entrepreneur, and [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] politician.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nndb.com/people/590/000207966/|title=Steve Poizner|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://wn.com/steve_poizner_on_encore_career_institute|title=Steve Poizner On Encore Career Institute|work=World News}}</ref>\n* [[Rex Tillerson]],<ref>[[Rex Tillerson]]</ref> former [[United States Secretary of State]], former chairman, president, and CEO of [[Exxon Mobil Corporation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/rex-tillerson/|title=Rex Tillerson|author=Christopher Helman|work=Forbes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0-MDAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA47&lpg=PA47&dq=rex+tillerson+tejas&source=bl&ots=8p9tMtRCaG&sig=hb_UTSYPbsR5a8V8I2zXM0jU_7Y&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ibFsUcTLMKHXygHd-oGQDA&ved=0CD8Q6AEwAw#v=onepage&q=rex%20tillerson%20tejas&f=false|title=The Alcalde|publisher=}}</ref>\n* [[Malcolm Wallace]],<ref name=\"Valley Morning Star; October 24, 1951\">{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=TU EX-Student Leader Jailed In Slaying; Malcolm E. Wallace Charged in Death of Golf Professional |work=Valley Morning Star |location=Harlingen, Texas |date=October 24, 1951 |page=1 }}</ref> former UT student body president, [[economist]] for the [[United States Department of Agriculture]],<ref name=\"Jones\">{{cite news |last1=Jones |first1=Garth |author-link1= |date=August 14, 1985 |title=Federal Official's Death Certificate Ordered Changed |url=https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=l1wdAAAAIBAJ&sjid=E1kEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6821%2C3251761 |newspaper=The Victoria Advocate |location=Victoria, Texas |agency=AP |page=8A |accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref> and press secretary to then-[[United States Senator]] [[Lyndon B. Johnson]].<ref name=\"Dalton\">{{cite web |url=http://www.golftexas.com/departments/coursereviews/butler-pitch-putt.htm |title=Butler Pitch and Putt in Austin: Murder in the clubhouse, fun on the golf course |last1=Dalton |first1=Kyle |date= |website=www.golftexas.com |publisher= |accessdate=June 16, 2014}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[Collegiate secret societies in North America]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official|http://tejasclub.org/}}\n\n{{University of Texas at Austin|studentlife}}\n\n[[Category:Collegiate secret societies]]\n[[Category:Student societies in the United States]]\n[[Category:Student organizations established in 1925]]\n[[Category:University of Texas at Austin]]\n[[Category:1925 establishments in Texas]]\n", "name_user": "Chris the speller", "label": "safe", "comment": "cap", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tejas_Club"}
